## 2. Features Covered

CookieRadar is a WordPress plugin designed to help you implement a cookie
consent mechanism for your website visitors. It includes:

- Automatic detection of active WordPress plugins likely to set cookies,
  by comparison with a regularly updated internal database.
- A granular consent banner allowing visitors to accept, decline or
  customize their preferences by category (essential, functional,
  analytics, marketing).
- Blocking of third-party scripts until explicit visitor consent is obtained.
- Dynamic activation of third-party scripts after consent (Google Analytics,
  Meta Pixel, Hotjar, LinkedIn, TikTok and other detected services).
- Automatic generation of a "Cookie Policy" page on your website, dynamically
  updated whenever a cookie-using plugin is activated or deactivated.
- A WordPress dashboard to customize banner texts, display position and
  primary color without touching any code.
- Compatibility with major WordPress themes (Divi 5, Elementor, Gutenberg,
  custom themes) and major caching plugins (WP Rocket, W3 Total Cache,
  WP Super Cache, LiteSpeed Cache).
- Consent stored in localStorage with timestamp and 180-day expiration.

